@NODE "Introduction" "Introduction"

 @{FG SHINE}@{U}Introduction@{UU}:@{FG TEXT}

   AmiIPWatcher is a small proggie that shows your IP and HostName. It has
   many nice features:
   @{B}*@{UB} MUI interface. (Using MUIRexx!)
   @{B}*@{UB} It uses very little memory.
   @{B}*@{UB} It's small.
   @{B}*@{UB} It's very easy to use.
   @{B}*@{UB} You can check for new versions and Download them from the program.
   @{B}*@{UB} You can press a button in the About window or choose visit homepage
     from the menu to go to my homepage.
   @{B}*@{UB} It saves an IP/HostName log which you can view from the program.
   @{B}*@{UB} You can send the IP/HostName to AmIRC!
   @{B}*@{UB} You can send the IP/HostName to STRICQ!
@ENDNODE

@NODE "Disclaimer" "Disclaimer"

 @{FG SHINE}@{U}Disclaimer@{UU}:@{FG TEXT}

   You are using this program at your own risk. I'm NOT responsible for
   anything this program might do. (@{B}Although it shouldn't do any damage!@{UB})
@ENDNODE

@NODE "Copyright" "Copyright"

 @{FG SHINE}@{U}Copyright@{UU}:@{FG TEXT}

   AmiIPWatcher is ©Copyright Lorens Johansson 1998-1999.
   This program is E-Mailware... If you use it then please send me an E-Mail
   so I can see how many people who uses this program... That's all I ask.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "Requirements" "Requirements"

 @{FG SHINE}@{U}Requirements@{UU}:@{FG TEXT}

   · AmigaOS 2.0+ (Since ARexx was introduced in 2.0)
   · The following libraries in LIBS:
     - locale.library
     - rexxkuang.library v0.26 or newer!
     - rexxtricks.library
     - rmh.library
     - rxsocket.library
   · MUI installed.
   · You must have MUIRexx installed and a MUIRexx assign to it.
   · You must have openurl installed to use the 'Visit Homepage' function.
   · An internet stack MUST be running, ie you have to start for example
     Miami. But you @{B}DO NOT@{UB} have to be online!!!
@ENDNODE

@NODE "Install" "How to install"

 @{FG SHINE}@{U}How to install@{UU}:@{FG TEXT}

   · Copy the AmiIPWatcher directory wherever you want.
   · Make sure that you have the following libraries to LIBS:
     - locale.library
     - rexxkuang.library v0.26 or newer!
     - rexxtricks.library
     - rmh.library
     - rxsocket.library
   · Be sure that you have MUIRexx: assigned to where MUIRexx is.
   · You must have openurl installed to be able to use the 'Visit Homepage'
     function.
   · If you want it on your language then just copy the catalog!
   · That's it!
@ENDNODE

