@NODE "HowTo_Log" "How to Use - IP/HostName Log Window"

 @{FG SHINE}@{U}How to Use - IP/HostName Log Window@{UU}:@{FG TEXT}
@{FG SHINE}____________________________________________________________________________@{FG TEXT}
ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ
                               T H E   G U I
@{FG SHINE}____________________________________________________________________________@{FG TEXT}
ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ
    @{B}* List:@{UB}
      This list shows you the logfile.
    @{B}* Clear Log:@{UB}
      Deletes all entries in the log file.
    @{B}* Delete Entry:@{UB}
      Deletes the marked entry in the list. It doesn't delete the entry from
      the logfile, you must save the log.
    @{B}* Save Log:@{UB}
      Saves the log to AmiIPWatcher.log.
    @{B}* Log LocalHost:@{UB}
      Check this if you want to save localhost in the log file.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "HowTo_Version" "How to Use - Check Version Window"

 @{FG SHINE}@{U}How to Use - Check Version Window@{UU}:@{FG TEXT}
@{FG SHINE}____________________________________________________________________________@{FG TEXT}
ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ
                               T H E   G U I
@{FG SHINE}____________________________________________________________________________@{FG TEXT}
ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ
    @{B}* This version:@{UB}
      Shows what version you are using.
    @{B}* Available version:@{UB}
      Shows what version that is available on my homepage.
    @{B}* Check Version:@{UB}
      Connects via http to a file and checks whats the newest version is.
    @{B}* Download AmiIPWatcher:@{UB}
      Connects via http and downloads the AmiIPWatcher archive.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "HowTo_SendAmIRC" "How to Use - Send To AmIRC Prefs Window"

 @{FG SHINE}@{U}How to Use - Send To AmIRC Prefs Window@{UU}:@{FG TEXT}
@{FG SHINE}____________________________________________________________________________@{FG TEXT}
ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ
                               T H E   G U I
@{FG SHINE}____________________________________________________________________________@{FG TEXT}
ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ
    @{B}* AmIRC Message:@{UB}
      What message you want to send to AmIRC.
      Add %cX,Y for some colours, the ,Y is optional.
      Add %i for the IP/HostName.
    @{B}* STRICQ Message:@{UB}
      What message you want to send to STRICQ.
      Add %i for the IP/HostName.
    @{B}* Save:@{UB}
      Saves the changes and closes the window.
    @{B}* Cancel:@{UB}
      Close the window, and discard the changes.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "History" "History"

 @{FG SHINE}@{U}History@{UU}:@{FG TEXT}

   @{B}1.0 :@{UB} @{FG SHINE}1998-11-18 (10575 bytes)@{FG TEXT}
   · Made the MUI interface.
   · Shows the IP.
   · Shows the HostName.
   · Added the menus.
   · Added the "Copy to clipboard" function.
   · Wrote the Guide.

   @{B}1.1 :@{UB} @{FG SHINE}1998-12-08 (11046 bytes)@{FG TEXT}
   · Added popupmenus for the IP and the HostName field.

   @{B}1.2 :@{UB} @{FG SHINE}1998-12-22 ( 4769 bytes)@{FG TEXT}
   · Made the program much smaller. It was shrunk with 6250 bytes, that's
     56.5% smaller. I didn't remove ANY functions.
     AmiIPWatcher now loads up twice as fast and it's alot faster to use!

   @{B}1.3 :@{UB} @{FG SHINE}1999-01-08 ( 6290 bytes)@{FG TEXT}
   · Added the 'Check version' function. With this you can check for new
     versions directly through the program.
   · Disabled the three Refresh Rate menuitems that aren't working yet.

   @{B}1.4 :@{UB} @{FG SHINE}1999-01-10 ( 7903 bytes)@{FG TEXT}
   · You can press a button in the About window to visit my homepage.
     You can also choose Visit Homepage from the menu.
   · I added a Busy meter that shows activity in the Check Version window.
   · I now use HTTPJ instead of FTPGet, it's faster with HTTP connections
     instead of FTP connections (in this case), and safer for me! :-)

   @{B}1.5 :@{UB} @{FG SHINE}1999-01-12 ( 9437 bytes)@{FG TEXT}
   · Added an IP/HostName logging system. It logs the Date, Time, IP and the
     HostName everytime you refresh and the IP or HostName changes. It saves
     the log into AmiIPWatcher.log and you can view it from the menu
     'View Logfile'.

   @{B}1.53:@{UB} @{FG SHINE}1999-01-15 (11847 bytes)@{FG TEXT}
   · You can now choose if you want to log the localhost or not.
   · Added a 'Are you sure...' requester when you press Clear Log file.
   · Replaced the Bold labels in View Logfile with white labels.

   @{B}1.6 :@{UB} @{FG SHINE}1999-01-21 (12072 bytes)@{FG TEXT}
   · AmiIPWatcher doesn't use HTTPJ any more, it now uses rexxkuang11.library
     which is much better.
   · It now checks for bsdsocket.library before trying to use it.
   · Added some features to the IP/HostName Log window: Delete Entry and
     Save Log.
   · Added help bubbles.
   · Added the posibility to press the HELP key to take you to the
     corresponding node in the Guide.
   · Updated the Guide alot.

   @{B}1.63:@{UB} @{FG SHINE}1999-01-24 (11204 bytes)@{FG TEXT}
   · It now uses openurl.library. (Thanks to Bossman^!)
   · Optimized a bit. (Thanks to Bossman^!)

   @{B}1.7 :@{UB} @{FG SHINE}1999-05-05 (10716 bytes)@{FG TEXT}
   · Made the IP center in the string gadget.
   · Removed the borders around the IP and HostName strings.
   · Moved the Refresh Now to the AmiIPWatcher menu, and removed the shadowed
     Refresh rates, since they aren't used!

   @{B}2.0 :@{UB} @{FG SHINE}1999-05-09 (11832 bytes)@{FG TEXT}
   · Forgot to center the HostName in the string gadget... Silly me :)
   · Added localesupport!!! Please write some catalogs!!!

   @{B}2.1 :@{UB} @{FG SHINE}1999-09-17 (16347 bytes)@{FG TEXT}
   · Added the possibility to send the IP or HostName to AmIRC, with some
     text. Useful to advertise a FTP or such...
   · Changed my E-Mail Address and URL to HomePage.
   · Added the possibility to send the IP or HostName to the selected user
     in STRICQ.
   · sOCIETY^rSE did some work too. Thanks.
   · Added new Swedish Translation. (by Me)
   · Added new German Translation. (by sOCIETY^rSE)
   · Added new French Translation. (by Jerome Chesnot)
@ENDNODE

